com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.modifiers

Class Modifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jme3.scene.plugins.blender.modifiers.Modifier
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SubdivisionSurfaceModifier, TriangulateModifier

    public abstract class Modifier
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents an object's modifier. The modifier object can be varied and the user needs to know what is the type of it for the specified type name. For example "ArmatureModifierData" type specified in blender is represented by AnimData object from jMonkeyEngine.
    Author:
    Marcin Roguski (Kaelthas)

      • invalid

        protected boolean invalid
        This variable indicates if the modifier is invalid (true) or not (false).

      • modifying

        protected boolean modifying
        A variable that tells if the modifier causes modification. Some modifiers like ArmatureModifier might have no Armature object attached and thus not really modifying the feature. In such cases it is good to know if it is sense to add the modifier to the list of object's modifiers.

      • canBeAppliedMultipleTimes

        public static boolean canBeAppliedMultipleTimes(java.lang.String modifierType)
        Determines if the modifier can be applied multiple times over one mesh. At this moment only armature and object animation modifiers cannot be applied multiple times.
        Parameters:
        modifierType - the type name of the modifier
        Returns:
        true if the modifier can be applied many times and false otherwise
